All instructions and commands to play sticks are available in the help menu once you run play_sticks.py.

To install:
  $ git clone https://github.com/Chuckuckuk/Sticks.git
  $ cd Sticks
  $ python play_sticks.py

The AI options are as follows:
  braindead acts almost completely randomly.
  easy will attack you if it knows it can take a hand, otherwise it plays defensively.
  medium is a slightly smarter version of easy.
  minimax AI (written by Robert Parks) looks for moves that maximize its advantage over you.
    The depth setting for minimax dictates how many moves into the future it is allowed to calculate.
